<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-28T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-28T02:00:00-05:00" n="256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.30 Asiatic Fleet/661: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-28T15:00:00+08:00">December 28, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 28—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>36. Referring to the Consulate’s telegram No. 12 of November 12, 9 a.m.,
                            Standard Vacuum Oil Company has reluctantly arranged for shipment of
                            bulk gasoline from Shanghai to Tsingtao on Japanese vessels one of which
                            was permitted to discharge at wharf on December 25; another Japanese
                            vessel will bring oil to Tsingtao for Company on January 1.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>